9RLQQMRqDWT9yomkGSbeRkarUxJptPz5ihmU08S3j--TR6zQAKb58ZFu3tMT42IIZFi7toMkKhKPRZFCpE7jnmErCNSJDr3cpr2dfWbDIHGMfjeg9J3DKm8IKOwlOKy_tLwuELj296IRLKIb1uueJYykxb0EG_85z14cZe-QWGDq\\\",\\\"summary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating URLClassLoader failures**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering the potential issues with using URLClassLoader natively. There's a rule to catch Errors and verify, but I'm wondering if ClassNotFoundException, which is checked, could still happen in this context. What if the class isn’t available as a resource? I think catching RuntimeException might help. However, it seems like NativeImage doesn’t support URLClassLoader, and while a new URLClassLoader could be created, there's still a risk of class loading failure that could throw an Error.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_WhZ1T7ILseSzaBbB7Xa0pu82|fc_0d09153518c040920169fa6d6afda48190b78db47561a4f966\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/com.google.inject/guice/3.0/src/test/java/com_google_inject/guice/InnerMethodWrapperTest.java\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 2532, \"output\": 2349, \"cacheRead\": 23552, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 28433, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778019656175, \"responseId\": \"resp_0d09153518c040920169fa6d48d9c88190a376a42d84b1b5e6\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_WhZ1T7ILseSzaBbB7Xa0pu82|fc_0d09153518c040920169fa6d6afda48190b78db47561a4f966\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_google_inject.guice;\\n\\nimport java.lang.refle